	<img src="img/articles/rightside-logo.png" alt="Rightside Logo">
</p>
<p>
	<a href="http://www.rightsidecapital.com/">Right Side Capital</a> is a pre-seed investment firm. They prefer doing a stage or two earlier than series A. Right Side invests in companies raising $50-500k almost exclusively at valuations between $1-3m and they always give an answer, whether yes or no, within 2 weeks. 
</p>

<p>
	Their philosophy is, at the early stage, you can predict almost nothing about whether a startup will be successful. Therefore, making decisions based on the founding team or things like the distribution model and any progress the team may have made are their basis’ for investment, not the idea.
</p>

<p>
	Right Side differentiates itself by focusing their investment efforts outside of the Silicon Valley and New York. They will still make investments in these regions, but find that there are better valuations in less competitive markets.
</p>

<p class="text-center margin-top">
	<img src="img/articles/rightside-strip.jpg" alt="Rightside Comic Strip">
